how do i restore an ipod what does it mean to restore a ipod nano restore is something you do from itunes and it wipes everything off your ipod and takes it back to its original settings so you'll have to start again from scratch this is a last resort before you try restoring try a reset this is done on the ipod and just reboots it and clears errors you slide the hold switch to the on and then off position then hold down the centre button and the menu top part of the wheel together until the apple logo appears the screen will go black for a while and then it should reappear and everything should work fine if it doesn't you might have a more serious problem which a restore might help make sure you backup all your files and music before you do that choose consolidate from the advanced menu in itunes to make sure all your music is collected in the itunes folder and then copy the itunes folder to your backup location IPod ITunes IPod mini Apple Computer Apple typography ITunes Music Store Mouse (computing) IPod shuffle ILife System/36 Windows 2000 Online music store FairPlay Backup Danger Hiptop PlayStation Portable Advanced Audio Coding IMac Redundant array of independent disks Windows Vista Digital rights management Digital audio player Object Desktop Screenshot Walkman Mac OS X v10.4 Windows XP QuickTime IPod photo Final Fantasy Gramophone record Apple Macintosh History of the graphical user interface Embedded system Napster (pay service) We Belong Together Floppy disk Creative Zen Mac OS history Vorbis System 7 (Macintosh) Start Menu Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis IBM PC compatible RealNetworks Disc jockey Palm OS Bluetooth Winning Streak U2 (band) System/34 Steve Jobs H.264/MPEG-4 AVC Game Boy Micro System 6 Resident Evil 2 ZX Spectrum SonicStage Mach kernel Macromedia Flash MP3 DDRMAX: Dance Dance Revolution Atari 8-bit family Slide rule Gmail Computer virus Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME (North America) The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (film) Windows Explorer S